  "prompt": "3 block with mas 6kg,9kg,10kg are connected as shown.The coefficient of friction between the table & 10kg block is 0.20.find; acceleration of system?",
  "response": "To find the acceleration of the system, we need to analyze the forces acting on each block. Let's denote the blocks as follows:\n\n- Block 1 (6 kg)\n- Block 2 (9 kg)\n- Block 3 (10 kg) with a coefficient of friction \u03bc = 0.20 between the table and the block.\n\nWe assume Block 1 and Block 2 are hanging off the table and are connected to Block 3, which is on the table. Block 1 and Block 2 are connected to Block 3 by pulleys.\n\nLet \\( T_1 \\) be the tension in the rope connected to Block 1, and \\( T_2 \\) be the tension in the rope connected to Block 2. The acceleration of the system is \\( a \\).\n\n**Forces acting on Block 1:**\n- Gravitational force (weight) = \\( 6g \\)\n- Tension \\( T_1 \\)\n\nUsing Newton\u2019s 2nd Law:\n\\[ 6g - T_1 = 6a \\]\n\n**Forces acting on Block 2:**\n- Gravitational force (weight) = \\( 9g \\)\n- Tension \\( T_2 \\)\n\nUsing Newton\u2019s 2nd Law:\n\\[ 9g - T_2 = 9a \\]\n\n**Forces acting on Block 3:**\n- Tension \\( T_1 \\) and \\( T_2 \\) pulling it horizontally.\n- Friction force \\( = \\mu \\cdot N \\) where \\( N \\) is the normal force. Since Block 3 is on the table, \\( N = 10g \\).\n\\[ \\text{Friction force} = \\mu \\cdot N = 0.20 \\cdot 10g = 2g \\]\n\nUsing Newton\u2019s 2nd Law:\n\\[ T_1 + T_2 - \\text{Friction force} = 10a \\]\n\\[ T_1 + T_2 - 2g = 10a \\]\n\nNow, we have three equations:\n\nEquation 1: \\( 6g - T_1 = 6a \\)\nEquation 2: \\( 9g - T_2 = 9a \\)\nEquation 3: \\( T_1 + T_2 - 2g = 10a \\)\n\nTo solve these equations, first express \\( T_1 \\) and \\( T_2 \\) in terms of \\( a \\):\n\nFrom Equation 1:\n\\[ T_1 = 6g - 6a \\]\n\nFrom Equation 2:\n\\[ T_2 = 9g - 9a \\]\n\nSubstitute \\( T_1 \\) and \\( T_2 \\) into Equation 3:\n\\[ (6g - 6a) + (9g - 9a) - 2g = 10a \\]\n\\[ 15g - 15a - 2g = 10a \\]\n\\[ 13g - 15a = 10a \\]\n\\[ 13g = 25a \\]\n\\[ a = \\frac{13g}{25} \\]\n\nUsing \\( g \\approx 9.8 \\, \\text{m/s}^2 \\):\n\\[ a = \\frac{13 \\times 9.8}{25} \\approx \\frac{127.4}{25} \\approx 5.096 \\, \\text{m/s}^2 \\]\n\nTherefore, the acceleration of the system is approximately \\( 5.1 \\, \\text{m/s}^2 \\).",
